*url*: the God of Thunder is sentenced to die!*

*url*: having to fight dinosaurs one moment and then soldier from the future the next!*

*description*: *After busting up a group of train robbers hired by Kang the Conqueror
*url*: the three time-traveling Avengers and the heroes of the old west learn how to break into Kang's citadel.*

*description*: *Thor
*url*: Moondragon and Immortus travel back to the year 1873 searching for their missing comrade!*

*description*: *Odin believes himself to be the Egyptian god Atum-Re and he's looking to destroy Thor - not knowing that he's actually his own son!*

*Yellowjacket pushes himself too far fighting off Toad and Whirlwind. Now
*thumbnail*: Scarlet Witch and Vision return from their almost-blissful honeymoon. Wasp awakens from her coma to the relief of her teammates.*

*url*: Iron Man and Moondragon travel to Doom's castle in Latveria. Whirlwind
*thumbnail*: a villain with an obsessive crush on Wasp

*The Wasp is gravely injured by the Stranger's attack

*url*: and Vision and Scarlet Witch taking time off for married life

*url*: the Absorbing Man just may be unstoppable. Can Thor use his wits to outduel the overpowered menace? And who will make a major sacrifice to ensure the life of Jane Foster?*

*The Vision discovers that Ultron played a significant role in his transformation from human to sentient A.I. Moondragon tells Mantis that she is the runner-up "Celestial Madonna"
*url*: should Mantis prove unworthy of the title.*

*thumbnail*: Hercules and Sif prepare for the threat that is Kamo Tharn.*

*year*: Moondragon shows up to the abandoned Avengers Mansion

*description*: *Loki and his army are winning the war and Thor and the US army might have to consider a final

*The Celestial Madonna is Mantis! The Avengers are still stuck in the realm of Limbo
*url*: with the newly-formed Legion of the Unliving. This legion consists of villainous foes past and present who have been resurrected by Immortus.*

*year*: Mantis is visited by an astral form of Swordsman
column7: which leaves her both confused and scared.*

*description*: *The spirit of Armak arrears to cause problems for the God of Thunder. Plus
*url*: will Jane Foster recover from her injuries?*

*description*: *The devastation of the Wrecking Crew continues! Plus
*url*: the introduction of a Gamma Bomb raises the stakes!*

*url*: with the Priests of Pama. However
*thumbnail*: their trip takes an unexpected turn when the team is greeted by three old enemies; Radioactive Man

*url*: Hercules! Can Thor stop a mad-with-rage Hercules?*

*url*: but is Steve Rogers a match for the Golden Archer?*

One of the two women at the Mansion will be the Madonna that Kang must "sire an heir with." *url*: member of the Inhuman royal family

*url*: will Thor and Herc be able to neutralize Ego

*description*: *Steve Rogers has had enough! The Star-Spangled Soldier renounces his Captain America identity... for good!*

*thumbnail*: more of Mantis' mysterious past revealed!*

*thumbnail*: has Thor returning to planet Rigel? The mystery of the Black Stars revealed.*

*thumbnail*: and the Scarlet Witch realize they're on the same side before it's too late?*

*description*: *Xorr bites off more than he can chew when he attempts to eat a star. On Midgard

*url*: Dormammu makes Loki an offer he can't refuse!*

*description*: *Return of the 4-D Man! And this time
*url*: Mercurio brought an army! Will Thor and company be trapped in the mines of the Dark Nebula?*

*url*: she is retrieved by Swordsman's partner
*thumbnail*: Mantis. With the current roster depleted
*year*: the Swordsman and Mantis are given a second chance to join the team of heroes. But will the two scoundrels prove their worth?*

*url*: the Avengers receive more hate mail than ever. Turns out
*thumbnail*: "normal" folk are offended by a romance between a sentient robot and a mutant. The Avengers are attacked by the "Living Bombs"
*year*: a group of extremists who believe the Avengers are destroying American values.*

*url*: Thor finds that all Asgardians are missing...and in their stead- Lizardmen from beyond the stars!*

*url*: a mythic hero from Africa who wants Panther to return to his African roots.*

*url*: the Black Widow becomes an official member of the Avengers team

*url*: Thor's battle with the Rock Trolls heats up
*thumbnail*: as the other heroes of Earth rally to help.*

*url*: and will he prevent Thor from being reunited with Lady Sif? Check out this smack down in London town!*

*url*: where are Sif and Karnilla headed?*

*url*: Black Panther returns from a strange mission with Daredevil.*

*When Sporadik
*thumbnail*: dies from a sudden heart attack
*year*: the Avengers suspect foul-play. Featuring Thor in his alter-ego guise of Dr. Donald Blake!*

*thumbnail*: the Avengers must call on teammates past and present to save the fallen hero.*

*url*: Hawkeye fills the Avengers in on how he returned to Earth and found Hercules.*

*url*: they must turn to the next order of business - locate the missing Avenger

*thumbnail*: and all the hosts of Asgard? No one but Mangog! The Warriors Three provide necessary backup.*

*url*: Loki has stolen Odin's ring making him rightful ruler! Can Thor stop Loki before he attacks his first target- Earth?*

*url*: the green brute is teleported away!*

*description*: *You've waited long enough. The startling
*thumbnail*: mind-boggling secret of Infinity! Another legend is born.*

*thumbnail*: "Dr. Blake" is able to apprehend both villains
